  "link": "https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/success\/myers-v-meltesen\/",
  "title": { "rendered": "Myers v. Meltesen" },
  "content": {
    "rendered": "\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\">\n<p id=\"block-6eeb7f61-aba1-4a02-8ca4-6442f4e4a41c\">Our client was riding his motorcycle in Burbank, CA. He was driving in a lane that began to merge with the lane next to him. The driver next to him was in a sedan that was not paying attention as they were traveling about 40 mph. The sedan merged right into our client causing our client&#8217;s motorcycle to tilt to the left. As the motorcycle tilted, our client&#8217;s foot was caught between the pavement and his motorcycle, which dragged for some time. Our client was taken to the hospital where he had screws inserted into his foot.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We contacted the insurance company to see if they would settle as our client now suffered from a permanent disability. Our client&#8217;s doctor said that while he would walk again, he would never be able to be as active as he had been prior to the accident. Our client was a highly active military veteran that would run marathons as a hobby.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The insurance company would only offer our client $30,000 to $40,000. We immediately sued. After exchanging some discovery in the lawsuit, the insurance company quickly folded and offered our client $410,000.00 to settle. <\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/iStock-660523594.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/murphlaw.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/07\/iStock-660523594-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"personal injury lawyer\" class=\"wp-image-3886\" width=\"520\" height=\"315\"\/><\/a><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n",
    "protected": false
  },
  "excerpt": {
